description.p:
The previous invention of MP-A and MP-T machines with stationary, brushless current tubes is expanded into MP-T II machines that include


(i) “flat” magnets in lieu of Halbach arrangements, thereby increasing the power density;

(ii) “triple S-ribbons” with 180° turns or either of two types in “rims” that greatly simplify machine construction;

(iii) improved cooling and lubrication by two alternative methods.
